casebody.data:
O’Rourke v. Monaghan. (Common Pleas of New York City and County, General Term. December 19, 1889.) Appeal from seventh district court.

Argued before Van Hoesen, P. J., and Bookstaver, J.

Mr. Brunneman, for appellant. J. Kearney, for respondent.

No opinion. Ordered that the judgment be reversed, new trial ordered, costs to abide the event.
